# ─── Build outputs ────────────────────────────────────────────────
# `dist/` contains both the TypeScript build artifacts AND the
# electron-builder release outputs (.dmg, .exe, .blockmap, latest.yml).
# Neither belongs in source control — TS output is reproducible from
# `npm run build`; release artifacts live on GitHub Releases.
dist/
out/
build/Release/
build/Debug/
*.tsbuildinfo

# ─── Dependencies ─────────────────────────────────────────────────
node_modules/

# ─── Signing certificates (defense in depth) ──────────────────────
# These should never live in source control. Even if a developer
# accidentally `git add`s a cert, this list catches it before the
# commit lands. Real cert plumbing is env-var driven (CSC_LINK,
# APPLE_API_KEY, WIN_CSC_LINK) and decoded from base64 at build
# time on CI runners — never on disk in the repo.
*.p12
*.pfx
*.p8
*.cer
*.pem
*.key

# ─── Secrets ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Resend API keys, Cloudinary credentials, signing passwords,
# notarization Apple-ID app-specific passwords. .env* covers all
# common dotenv variants (.env, .env.local, .env.production, etc.).
.env
.env.*

# ─── Logs ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Electron + electron-builder log to stderr but some integrations
# write log files alongside the source tree. Excluding these
# prevents accidentally committing logs that include filesystem
# paths, Apple notarization request IDs, or other diagnostic info.
*.log
npm-debug.log*
yarn-debug.log*
yarn-error.log*
pnpm-debug.log*

# ─── OS noise ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────
.DS_Store
Thumbs.db
ehthumbs.db
Desktop.ini

# ─── Editor noise ─────────────────────────────────────────────────
.vscode/
.idea/
*.swp
*.swo
*~
